name: Mini Spinach and Crab Quiche
author: Everettrj
summary: Bite-size mini quiches packed with flavor and nutrition. They can be filled with a variety of your favorite meats, cheeses, and veggies, but spinach and crab are a favorite in our family! Serve warm topped with a dollop of sour cream and salsa or just alone as a great portable and easy breakfast.
ingredients: ¼ cup milk, or as needed
¼ cup shredded sharp Cheddar cheese
salt and ground black pepper to taste
¾ cup imitation crab meat, finely chopped
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Spray 24 miniature muffin cups with cooking spray
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat and cook onion until softened, about 2 minutes
Stir spinach into onion and cook, stirring often, until spinach is wilted and onions are translucent, about 3 more minutes
Beat eggs with milk in a large bowl until thoroughly combined; stir in Cheddar, Asiago, and Parmesan cheeses and season with salt and black pepper
Divide spinach mixture into the prepared muffin cups (about 1 teaspoon per cup) and top spinach with imitation crab meat
Slowly and carefully pour egg-cheese mixture over the imitation crab, filling the mini muffin cups just to the top
Bake in the preheated oven until the egg is set, 12 to 15 minutes
